span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">l opportunity for local opposition groups to voice their concerns.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">(in the case of R39, all attempts by a local opposition group to engage with the governors and discuss important issues were declined, including one occasion when R39 cancelled a presentati</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">on they were due to give to a parish council meeting when an opposition group was also granted permission to make a presentation)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Funding can be approved without planning permission</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">It would appear that the EFA can approve funding for a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Free</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">School</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> even b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">efore planning permission is granted for the school to be built. This leads to the suspicion that the DoE would intervene if permission is refused by local planning committees.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">(in the case of R39, funding has been approved in spite of the fact that planni</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">ng permission for a temporary site was refused - the planning application for the permanent site has still not been submitted)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">unding </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">can</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> approved in areas with a surplus of school places</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The EFA is happy to fund Free Schools in areas where there is n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o shortage of school places.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">(in the case of R39, the governors maintain that competition is good and will raise standards across all schools, and yet they have struggled to fill their places and the 4 existing state secondary schools in the area have all </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">lost a few pupils) </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-siz